com.concordium.sdk.responses.blockitemsummary

Class AccountTransactionDetails

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.concordium.sdk.responses.blockitemsummary.AccountTransactionDetails

  • public class AccountTransactionDetails
extends Object
    Details of a transaction with a sender account.

    Users should always check whether the AccountTransactionDetails is isSuccessful() or not. If this returns false, then one should consult the rejectReasonType for why the transaction failed. If the transaction was successful then first check the type via getType() and use the corresponding getter for getting the concrete event.
